-- Italy economy to shrink by 0.4-0.5 percent in 2012: minister
-- 
-- Sun Dec 4, 2011 4:23pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/12/04/us-italy-growth-idUSTRE7B30UE20111204

 

 ROME  (Reuters) - Italy's economy is expected to shrink by 0.4-0.5 percent in 2012, and remain flat in 2013, Deputy Economy Minister Vittorio Grilli told a news conference on Sunday. 
 Grilli said budget measures unveiled by the government on Sunday would help compensate weaker growth. (Reporting By Catherine Hornby)